==> scripting/jruby <==

JRuby is used unmodified as a possible backend for the scripting module. You do
not need to use the scripting module to use SxE or JRuby for a Ruby backend,
both are provided as continence.

Source code can be found at the following locations:
	- http://jruby.org/download
	- http://jruby.org/contribute
	- https://github.com/jruby/jruby

Please refer to scripting/jruby/build.gradle for the version used. At this time
of writing, it is version: '1.7.4'. A summery of the license is presented below:


	JRuby is Copyright (c) 2007-2013 The JRuby project, and is released
